title: Boxing. Manny Pacquiao (31 fights)
description:
Emmanuel Dapidran Pacquiao (born December 17, 1978), known as Manny 
"Pac-Man" Pacquiao is a Filipino professional boxer. He is the former WBC 
Lightweight world champion, WBC Super Featherweight world champion, IBF 
Super Bantamweight world champion, and WBC Flyweight world champion. 
He has also held the Ring Magazine titles for Featherweight, Super 
Featherweight, and Light Welterweight divisions. For his achievements, he 
became the first Filipino and Asian boxer to win five world titles in five 
different weight divisions. He is currently the IBO and Ring Magazine Light 
Welterweight champion and is rated by the Ring Magazine as the #1 
pound-for-pound boxer in the world. He is also the first boxer to win the lineal 
championship in four different weight classes.
